“These are the people who are not going to be joking around with criminals, they will be required to take imminent action,” Ngcobo said. 
With immediate effect the reserve will be closed from 6pm to 6am and all visitors will be required to sign in and out.
The department said that it will be engaging with The Friends of Bruman Bush as stakeholders to help manage the reserve.AdChoicesADVERTISINGinRead invented by Teads

“Together with the members of the community we will then manage this reserve, have them as stakeholders so that they can bring to our attention things they see here and how this area should be managed,”said Ngcobo.
Ngcobo said the fence will be erected as soon as council allows and the management team has indicated that the fence will take about one month to install along the 4.5km perimeter of the reserve.

 







