“This is not going to be a free area for criminals, with the measures that we are going to propose people will tell you that it is safer in six months,”he said
Morningside councillor Martin Meyer said he was happy with the plan put forward but urged Ngcobo to close the reserve until additional security is in place.

“I feel strongly about this until we have that extra security in place we cannot put other peoples lives in danger,” Jsaid Meyer.
Meyer urged the community not just to rely on SAPS and politicians to make their area safer.
“It is the community together with the police and politicians who need to work together to improve our city and improve our parks,” Meyer said.

 







